TITLE: Wyoming college wrestlers injured during bear attack, left 'blood-soaked,' coach says
SUMMARY: Two college wrestlers in Wyoming were injured during a bear attack and two others were left “blood-soaked," their coach told Fox News.

TITLE: New York man dies after falling onto subway tracks during fight: police
SUMMARY: A 40-year-old New York City man died Monday afternoon after falling onto the subway tracks following a physical altercation with another man, police said.

TITLE: NYPD releases surveillance video of $500,000 jewelry heist in Manhattan
SUMMARY: Surveillance video released by the NYPD shows three suspects smashing display cases at a jewelry store in Manhattan before making off with $500,00 worth of valuables.

TITLE: Ghislaine Maxwell says she feels ‘so bad’ for Prince Andrew in first interview since 20-year prison sentence
SUMMARY: Jeffrey Epstein cohort Ghislaine Maxwell, speaking from her Florida jail cell, said in a recent interview she feels "so bad" for her "dear friend" Prince Andrew.

TITLE: Oklahoma police name person of interest in murders of four men, locate dismembered remains in river
SUMMARY: Oklahoma police recovered the dismembered bodies of four missing men in a river on Friday and have identified a person of interest in the murder investigation.

TITLE: Stockton serial killer: How California police tracked down shadowy murder suspect
SUMMARY: Suspected Stockton serial killer Wesley Brownlee is accused of ambushing seven people in an 18-month span before police arrested him over the weekend.

TITLE: John Hinckley Jr. admits to killing James Brady in attempt on President Reagan's life
SUMMARY: In an interview, John Hinckley Jr., admitted to being responsible for the death of James Brady, who was shot during the attempted assassination of President Ronald Regan

TITLE: Maine AG rules officer justified in shooting despite 37-foot distance
SUMMARY: Maine's Attorney General Aaron Frey has decided that a police officer was justified in shooting a man three times from a distance of 37 feet, rather than 15 feet as originally stated.

TITLE: MA dog walker surrounded by pack of coyotes north of Boston
SUMMARY: A dog walker was surrounded by a pack of wild coyotes while walking a dog north of Boston over the weekend. Police were able to bring the dog walker and the dog to safety.

TITLE: Fomer Native American boarding school in Kansas to be searched for buried indigenous children
SUMMARY: Kansas officials will search the grounds of a former Native American boarding school to determine if any indigenous children are buried there.
